
[1]amorpha

   AMORPH'A, n. [Gr. a neg and form.]

   False or bastard indigo. The plant is a native of Carolina,
   constituting a genus. It rises, with many irregular stems, to the
   height of twelve or fourteen feet; the leaves, beautifully pinnated,
   are of an admired green color, and its purple flowers grow in spikes of
   seven or eight inches long. Of this plant has been made a course kind
   of indigo.
